Description: Body sherd of Milesian Fikellura pottery oinochoe; exterior, white slip: painted overlapping narrow rosettes.
Curator's comments: Cook (CVA BM 8, 8 no. 4) groups this sherd with British Museum 1924,1201.1053 and 1949,0516.18, 1888,0601.556.b, 1886,0601.556.c (the findspot for this sherd is specified as the Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi) and 1949,0516.15, with the comment that it and 1888,0601.556.c may come from a different vase. The modern inscription on interior in ink 'NA124' indicates the sherd once belonged to the Cambridge Museum of Classical Archaeology.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (p. 8, no. 4d, pl. 8, no. 4d)
